POLICE officers from the West Rand cluster know the importance of divine intervention.Last Thursday, officers from the Men for Change forum hosted an event at Kagiso Community Hall in Mogale City. The cops gathered to thank God for protecting all law enforcement officers in the area.West Rand commander Major-General Annah Mateisie said: &ldquo;The best protection comes from God, who gives power to fight thugs.&rdquo; The event started on Kagiso Avenue where police, traffic cops and correctional services officials marched together to the main venue. Randfontein Police Station commander Brigadier Jacob Manamela said: &ldquo;Law enforcement officials have been appointed by God to bring peace to communities. &ldquo;Those who are appointed to destroy us cannot overcome the power of prayer.&rdquo;